Type: Package
Package: coLCA
Title: Companion Package to 'poLCA'
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Naoko", "Skiada", email = "naoko.skiada@kcl.ac.uk", role =
    c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8575-9846"))
Maintainer: The package maintainer <naoko.skiada@kcl.ac.uk>
Description: This package adds new and convenience functions to the 'poLCA' package.  
    New functions: calculations of the consistent Akaike Information Criterion (cAIC), 
    sample-adjusted Bayesian Information Criterion (aBIC), entropy and
    Lo-Mendel-Rubin Likelihood Ratio tests (LMR LRT). Convenicence functions: a
    function that estimates all latent class models required by the user
    and outputs a comparison table with model selection statistics and
    functions that create spider or line charts using the item response
    probabilities.
License: `use_mit_license()`, `use_gpl3_license()`
Imports:
    dplyr,
    foreach,
    poLCA,
    tidyLPA (>= 1.0.5)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
